org.hibernate.metamodel.model.domain.spi

Interface Readable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    BagPersistentAttribute<O,E>, IdentifierBagAttribute<O,E>, ListPersistentAttribute<D,E>, MapPersistentAttribute<D,K,V>, NonIdPersistentAttribute<O,J>, PluralPersistentAttribute<O,C,E>, SetPersistentAttribute<D,E>, StateArrayContributor<J>, VersionDescriptor<O,J>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractNonIdSingularPersistentAttribute, AbstractPluralPersistentAttribute

    public interface Readable
    Inverse of Writeable for types which can be read back from the database via a simplified 2-phase process. Generally speaking, reading/loading is defined via DomainResult and Initializer.
    See Also:
    Writeable

    • Method Detail

      • hydrate

        default Object hydrate(Object jdbcValues,
                       SharedSessionContractImplementor session)
        An array shaping method.
        "API Note:"
        The incoming `jdbcValues` might be a single object or an array of objects depending on whether this Readable reported one or more SqlSelections. The return follows the same rules. For a composite-value, an `Object[]` would be returned representing the composite's "simple state". For entity-value, the return would be its id's "simple state" : again a single `Object` for simple ids, an array for composite ids. All others return a single value. todo (6.0) : this may not be true for ANY mappings - verify - those may return the (id,discriminator) tuple

      • resolveHydratedState

        default Object resolveHydratedState(Object hydratedForm,
                                    ExecutionContext executionContext,
                                    SharedSessionContractImplementor session,
                                    Object containerInstance)
        Given a hydrated representation of this Readable, resolve its domain representation.

        E.g. for a composite, the hydrated form is an Object[] representing the "simple state" of the composite's attributes. Resolution of those values returns the instance of the component with its resolved values injected.

        "API Note:"
